      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, quick question for my dissertation. if i'm looking at a p-value of 0.06 in my results, people are saying it's \"not significant,\" but the trend looks pretty clear in the charts. can you explain why we can't just call it significant or why that threshold matters so much theoretically?",
